<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
The specific epithet refers to Australian female carpenter bees 
<taxonomicName authority="(Koptortosoma)" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Xylocopa (Koptortosoma)</taxonomicName>
sp., because of its superficial resemblance with respect to hair and wing colouration.
</paragraph>
